members.name: getAccessibleIcon
members.comment: Returns the icon for the element renderer, as the only item of an array of AccessibleIcons or a null array if the renderer component contains no icons.

return: an array containing the accessible icon or a null array if none

members.name: getAccessibleAction
members.comment: Gets the AccessibleAction associated with this object that supports one or more actions.

implSpec: Returns the AccessibleAction for this AccessibleJListChild as follows: First getListCellRendererComponent of the ListCellRenderer for the component at the "index in parent" of this child is called. Then its AccessibleContext is fetched and that AccessibleContext's AccessibleAction is returned. Note that if an AccessibleAction is not found using this process then this object with its implementation of the AccessibleAction interface is returned.
return: AccessibleAction if supported by object; else return null

members.name: doAccessibleAction
members.comment: Performs the specified action on the object.

implSpec: If i == 0 selects this AccessibleJListChild by calling JList.this.setSelectedIndex(indexInParent) and then returns true; otherwise returns false.
param: i - zero-based index of actions
return: true if the action was performed; otherwise false

members.name: getAccessibleActionDescription
members.comment: Returns a description of the specified action of the object.

implSpec: If i == 0 returns the action description fetched from UIManager.getString("AbstractButton.clickText"); otherwise returns null.
param: i - zero-based index of the actions
return: a String description of the action

members.name: getAccessibleActionCount
members.comment: Returns the number of accessible actions available in this object If there are more than one, the first one is considered the "default" action of the object.

implSpec: Returns 1, i.e. there is only one action.
return: the zero-based number of actions in this object

param: parent - the parent
indexInParent - the index in the parent

name: javax.swing.JList$AccessibleJList$AccessibleJListChild
comment: This class implements accessibility support appropriate for list children.
